article.headline: Dartmouth 53, Princeton 43
article.story: HANOVER, N.H. (AP) -- John Ball and Leon Pattman scored 14 points apiece Friday as Dartmouth completed its first two-game season sweep of Princeton since the 1945-46 season with a 53-43 victory. Ball added a game-high 10 rebounds while Alex Barnett had seven points, seven rebounds and four blocks for Dartmouth (9-15, 4-7 Ivy League), which won the first matchup between the teams two weeks ago in New Jersey. Luke Owings led Princeton (11-13, 2-8 Ivy League) with 15 points and seven rebounds in 18 minutes off the bench in the rematch. Dartmouth led by as many as 11 points before taking a 26-21 lead at halftime. Both teams had hot hands in the first half with Princeton shooting 52.9 percent from the field and Dartmouth 52.2 percent. Trailing 36-25 early in the second half, Princeton got 10 points from Owings in a 16-4 run capped by an Owings 3-pointer that put the Tigers up 41-40 for their only lead of the game. Dartmouth took the lead back on a twisting layup by Pattman, who scored five points in a 7-0 run that gave the Big Green a 47-41 lead with 1:31 to play. After a Lincoln Gunn basket in the paint made it a four-point game with 1:08 to play, Dartmouth ran off the final six points to close the game on a 13-2 run.
